# Lead Quanta Acceptance Criteria

Use these as the definition of done for platform features. See **platform-personas**, **platform-workflows**, and **platform-architecture** for supporting detail.

## 8. Developer acceptance criteria

| Area | Acceptance criterion |
|------|---------------------|
| **Persona access** | Each persona lands on a relevant dashboard and sees only permitted features, fields, and actions |
| **Deal slip workflow** | Every trade has a deal slip before approval and settlement, except system-configured exempt activities approved by governance |
| **Control checks** | Required limit, compliance, rating, tenor, and eligibility checks run before approval. Breaches must not disappear |
| **Approval routing** | Routing based on amount, asset class, fund, counterparty, exception type, and approval mandate |
| **Settlement control** | Back Office raises or confirms settlement instructions from an approved deal slip. Traders cannot confirm settlements |
| **Register integrity** | Investment register updates only after settlement confirmation or an approved lifecycle event |
| **Accounting trigger** | Finance outputs generated from approved, settled, and classified records |
| **Audit evidence** | All changes, approvals, returns, rejections, settlements, overrides, and postings are traceable |
| **Exception management** | Every exception has an owner, due date, status, approval evidence, and closure comment |
| **Reporting** | Dashboards reconcile to investment register, accrual engine, valuation records, and GL status |

## Build priority

### MVP sequence (build in this order)

```
Trade Blotter → Deal Slip → Automated Checks → Approval → Settlement
  → Investment Register → Accrual → Limits → Reports
```

Do not build downstream modules (accrual, limits, reports) against blotter or draft deal data — wire them to the register after settlement.

### Advanced sequence (post-MVP)

```
Valuation → Performance → Stress Analytics → GL Interface → Full ALCO and Board reporting
```

### Critical defect to avoid

**Never allow a trade to become an active holding without an approved deal slip and confirmed settlement.** This is the highest-risk defect in the system.
